tourBios.curYrHigh: Played in 19 Web.com Tour events, making four cuts. Finished 86th on the money list...Recorded his first Web.com Tour top 10 at the El Bosque Mexico Championship in April. Finished T4 on the strength of four sub-par rounds (68-71-68-69)...Qualified for his first U.S. Open in June, posting 74-80 to miss the cut. Flew from Seattle to his native Munich, Germany to play in the following week's BMW International Open on the European Tour, at the course he grew up playing. Posted rounds of 75-77 and missed the cut…Opened 68-66 at the Utah Championship in early August to claim his second top 10 of the year, a T8 with Lucas Lee and Ryan Blaum at the GC at Thanksgiving Point.

tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Joined PGA TOUR Latinoamérica with a T16 finish at the Qualifying Tournament in Sebring, Fla., in January…Finished the year having made 12 starts, with a T9 at the Ecuador Open in September his top performance...Was runner-up at Second Stage Web.com Tour Q-School event in November at Brooksville, Fla. to advance to Finals...Finished T8 at Web.com Tour Q-School in December, on the strength of a closing-round 65. 

2013: Made seven cuts in 14 starts on the Web.com Tour to finish No. 122 on the money list. His best finishes were T11 at the BMW Charity Pro-Am presented by SYNNEX Corporation and T19 at the Cox Classic presented by Lexus of Omaha. Finished T7 at the Puerto Rico Classic presented by Merrill Lynch in his only career start on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica.

 2012: Turned pro in August…Made one Web.com Tour start, missing the cut at the Nationwide Children's Hospital Invitational in Columbus, Ohio.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was a member of four state high school championship teams at Baylor School in Chattanooga...Won four college events, including the 2012 SoCon Championship and the 2012 NCAA Championship Bowling Green Regional. Was named to 2012 first-team Ping All-American team. Is only three-time Southern Conference Player of the Year (2010, 2011 and 2012). Had 15 career top-5s. Was on Dean's List all four years. Graduated in May 2012.
tourBios.personal: Son of Sophie and Klaus Jaeger...Has one sister, Michaela...Came to America in 2006 as an exchange student his junior year. Attended Baylor School in Chattanooga, where one of his high school teammates was current PGA TOUR member Harris English. Stayed on at Baylor for his senior year, then went to UT-Chattanooga...Favorite pro team is the Denver Broncos...Favorite golf courses to play are The Honors Course and Riviera CC..."Transformers" is his favorite movie...His favorite places to visit are New York and Singapore...The beach is his top vacation spot...Would like to trade places with Jack Nicklaus for a day...Miguel Ángel Jiménez, Harris English and Nicklaus would round out his dream foursome...Would be a rally car driver if he were not a golfer...Bucket list includes rally driving...Misses eating schnitzel...Grew up playing soccer and tennis.
